{
  "info": {
    "name": "Problem 5 — Product CRUD API",
    "description": "End-to-end Postman collection for the Problem 5 Product CRUD service (Express + TypeScript + Prisma + PostgreSQL).\n\n## How to use\n\n1. Start the server: `docker compose up -d && npm run dev` (see project README).\n2. Import this collection into Postman.\n3. Import `problem5.postman_environment.json` (or set the `baseUrl` collection variable).\n4. Open the **Smoke Test Flow** folder and click **Run** in the Collection Runner — it exercises the happy path end-to-end and captures `productId` for downstream requests.\n5. The remaining folders cover validation/404/edge-case scenarios and can be run individually or as a whole.\n\n## Conventions\n\n- `{{baseUrl}}` defaults to `http://localhost:3000`.\n- `{{productId}}` is populated by the **Smoke Test Flow** > *Create product* step.\n- `{{unknownId}}` is a well-formed CUID guaranteed not to exist.\n- `{{malformedId}}` is intentionally invalid to exercise the schema-level 400.\n- Every request has a Tests script asserting the expected status code and shape; the Collection Runner shows pass/fail.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "productId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "unknownId", "value": "cjld2cjxh0000qzrmn831i7rn", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "malformedId", "value": "not-a-cuid", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "00 — Smoke Test Flow",
      "description": "Ordered happy-path flow. Run this folder via the Collection Runner to exercise the full create → read → update → delete lifecycle. The Create step captures `productId` into a collection variable for the subsequent steps.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Health check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/health", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "health"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(200));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('envelope.success === true', () => pm.expect(json.success).to.eql(true));",
                  "pm.test('data.status === ok', () => pm.expect(json.data.status).to.eql('ok'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Create product (captures productId)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Smoke Mechanical Keyboard\",\n  \"description\": \"Hot-swappable 75% layout, used by the smoke flow\",\n  \"price\": 149.99,\n  \"category\": \"peripherals\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/products", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "products"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(201));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('envelope.success === true', () => pm.expect(json.success).to.eql(true));",
                  "pm.test('data.id is a string', () => pm.expect(json.data.id).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "pm.test('createdAt is ISO string', () => pm.expect(json.data.createdAt).to.match(/^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}T/));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('productId', json.data.id);",
                  "console.log('Captured productId:', json.data.id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "3. Get product by captured id",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/products/{{productId}}", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "products", "{{productId}}"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(200));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('id matches captured productId', () => pm.expect(json.data.id).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('productId')));",
                  "pm.test('name === Smoke Mechanical Keyboard', () => pm.expect(json.data.name).to.eql('Smoke Mechanical Keyboard'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "4. Patch price (partial update)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{ \"price\": 129.99 }",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/products/{{productId}}", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "products", "{{productId}}"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(200));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('price updated to 129.99', () => pm.expect(json.data.price).to.eql(129.99));",
                  "pm.test('name preserved (partial update)', () => pm.expect(json.data.name).to.eql('Smoke Mechanical Keyboard'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "5. Delete and verify 404 on subsequent get",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/products/{{productId}}", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "products", "{{productId}}"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 204', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(204));",
                  "pm.test('body is empty', () => pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.eql(''));",
                  "// Follow-up GET in this same script to confirm the row is gone.",
                  "pm.sendRequest({",
                  "  url: pm.collectionVariables.get('baseUrl') + '/api/products/' + pm.collectionVariables.get('productId'),",
                  "  method: 'GET'",
                  "}, (err, res) => {",
                  "  pm.test('subsequent GET returns 404', () => pm.expect(res.code).to.eql(404));",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
